{
    "task_summary": "Convert a non-negative integer to its binary representation without using Python's built-in bin() function.",
    "approach": "Iteratively divide the number by 2 and record the remainder until the number becomes zero. The remainders represent the binary digits in reverse order.",
    "code": "def int_to_binary(n):\n    if n == 0:\n        return '0'\n    binary_digits = []\n    while n > 0:\n        remainder = n % 2\n        binary_digits.append(str(remainder))\n        n //= 2\n    # Reverse the list to get the correct binary representation\n    binary_digits.reverse()\n    return ''.join(binary_digits)",
    "complexity": {
